special topics in group theory page 1 department colloquium tuesday january 17 2 30pm bldg 380 room 383 n laurent saloff coste cornell random walks from a geometric perspective abstract in this talk i will discuss random walk as a way to explore non commutative finitely generated groups the focus will be on the relations between various behaviors of random walk and the properties of the group from the view point of algebra and or coarse geometry i will attempt to give a broad view of the subject from harry kesten's 1958 ph d thesis to the present day
